description.plain:
Born in January of 2010 in Canterbury, Delta Sleep was driven by a desire to create fun and original, forward-thinking music. Their songs combines guitar driven melodies, held together by jazz influenced percussion and relentless bass, topped with sprinkles of passionate shouts and lulling chants. To coin Delta Sleep’s sound is a hard task indeed, but has once been described by a wise old man as an “enchanted battle between Don Cab and At The Drive-In for the city of Radiohead in the land of Faraquet”. Their playfulness invokes sugarcoated riffs, and their hospitality will warm you through on a crisp winter’s day.
Their live show is a force to reckoned with. Energetic, captivating and extremely tight, they win over their audience at every turn. They have shared the stage with bands such as Tera Melos, And So I Watch You From Afar, This Town Needs Guns, DDIMMIYYYY, Cougar, Tall Ships, Tubelord, Enemies, to name just a few.
Management, their 2nd EP, is set for release this May 2013 through Big Scary Monsters in the UK and HipHipHip in France. The EP release will coincide with a 2 week tour throughout the UK and northern Europe.

Source: http://www.last.fm/music/Delta+Sleep/+wiki

songs.title: Dustbusters
songs.embed_content: Read “Dustbusters” by Delta Sleep on Genius
songs.lyrics:
[Intro: Alan Watt]
"Waking up from a dream, going round and round and round. After a while once experiences begins to have a, what I would call “haven’t we been here before feeling?”. And then you begin wondering, where am I going? What do I want to happen? And of course as soon as you ask yourself that you begin to fantasize. And so I soon found myself at a great push-button place, with buttons available for every conceivable thing I could wish. All possible pleasures are available. You know you go “Going!” like that and here is Cleopatra, then press this button, and symphonic music. So I simply set myself to thinking through how far we could go? Now, you suddenly notice there’s a button labeled Surprise. You push that – and here we are."

In hiding you'll find the shadows of time will recite the words that you could not say, eloquently most oftenly misleads the words in the shadows will put you to sleep
Say, eloquence most oftenly misleads the words in the shadows will put you to sleep

A bird, crippled in flight, is unlikely to fall. It's wings will glide it to safety
Now run, open those arms
Set assumptions aside, surprises will (creep up on you)1EmbedShare URLCopyEmbedCopy

songs.title: Sans Soleil

description.plain:
The title literally translated means “Without Sun” This song is about leaving the city and civilization remembering the past and finding solace in the unknown but yet far more natural world.

Fitting within the albums themes of a dystopian future and existential realization this song furthers the story that “Ghost City” tells.

PROPOSED SUGGESTION: It also references a 1983 French documentary directed by Chris Marker going by the same title.
Its theme revovles around the beauty of Nature aswell as the dangers modern Society pose to it.

Devin “had most of the bones mapped out for this song before bringing it to the practice room. But it really became a whole different beast when the other guys added their parts. It went from being quite a mellow folky / finger picked guitar song, to a super power driven ultimate rock ballad.”

songs.title: El Pastor

description.plain:
As per Devin: “This is the first single we released from the album. Glen wrote the main guitar riff which is just so catchy, and Blake’s intro drum part just hooks you from the get go.

[…] The sample that plays out at the end of this song [was recorded] in a beautiful town called Tlaxcala. We stumbled across a group of young guys playing old traditional folk songs. They played this song for us, it was a truly beautiful moment. "

Most lyrics for this one are fairly self-explanatory as it sees our character expressing their confusion, awe and newfound love for the beauty of nature in full colour.

The title is Spanish – translating to “The Shepherd”, in reference to the different creatures and parts of nature the character is now “herding” because of her ability to freely roam the outside world. It can be implied it was changed to Spanish because of the Mexican sample at the end of the album version of the track.

songs.title: Afterimage

description.plain:
“While writing the vocal hook for the intro of “Sultans of Ping”, I knew I wanted to expand on it and write a full song that reprised a few hooks and melodies from the intro. This is that song. It also felt like a nice way to bookend the album with a similar theme to the intro but with a completely different feel.” – Devin.

The themes of reminiscence continue from Floater on this track and close the whole album off with a cyclical structure.

songs.title: Strongthany

description.plain:
Strongthany is the 10th song off of Delta Sleep’s 2016 Debut album Twin Galaxies. The song continues the narrative of the album by expressing hardships as aquatic and seafaring themes.

Opening with fast-paced drums and guitar this song is about things finally changing for the better for the protagonist of the album after all the hardships he has faced so far.

songs.title: After Dark

description.plain:
After Dark is the “abstract introduction to the […] world” of Ghost City – according to Devin Yuceil. It was one of the first riffs written for the album and some of the last written lyrics due to the nature of the timing of the song; a multi-metered 5/4+6/4+5/4+5/8 signature that Devin could hardly play and sing all at once.

It sees the protagonist of the story fantasising about leaving the city before actually attempting it in the later tracks.

songs.title: Dream Thang

description.plain:
As per Glen: “[Dream Thang is] Another one of those songs that really became a song in the studio. It really started as a bit of a filler riff that none of us knew what to do with – It was just a super delay / reverb soaked loop that went around and around without really going anywhere. I don’t think we really realised how big a hook it was going to be until we recorded it on the day.”

This song is essentially the character expressing her doubts about her plan, though with optimism – the title implies it could be a dream sequence, as from here on-wards she is out of the city for good.

songs.title: Floater

description.plain:
As per Devin: “This was the very last album song to be written. I had already written most of the song but the other guys were still unsure of their parts and certain structural elements, and we weren’t sure we were going to include it on the album. We actually finished writing it all together in the studio which was an amazing feeling, and along with both interludes was a first for us.”

All of the lyrics are self – explanatory, it sees our character finally at the end of her long journey being able to “unlock” her dreams. A sort of reminiscent theme is shown throughout, something that heavily carries over into Afterimage.

songs.title: A Casa

description.plain:
“Here is the series finale of Soft Sounds! 🙌 🎉 🎁

“A Casa” is a new song that we solidified in June 2020. We locked ourselves into Middle Farm studios (the same place we recorded Younger Years) and spent 5 days reconnecting and working on some new ideas after not having seen each other for several months due to that little thing called Covid-19. We parted ways after a really productive few days and haven’t played together since. But the good news is album 3 is well underway! 👌👍🤝

This version of “A Casa” came together after Dev finished the lyrics loosely inspired by the quarantine. He sent over his parts and we all pieced the song together separately, with whatever means and instruments we had, filming our performances on our phones in our respective quarantine locations. This video may not be as cinematic or impressive as the others but we thought it would be a nice way to tie up the whole series and give you a little glimpse of some new flavours we’ve been cooking up during the lockdown. We hope you like it and we hope you enjoyed Soft Sounds as much as we enjoyed putting it out into the world!
Thanks for your continued support, stay safe, and we’ll see you on the other side. Huge love,
Delta Sleep ❤️
xxx"

-Delta Sleep on Youtube
